00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:49.000
Begin by Removing the battery cover
The battery and the SD Card

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:21.000
On the front of the phone, remove the plastic
cover with the cell provider logo near the
bottom of the unit.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:04.000
You can now remove two t5 screws that were
underneith that cover

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:25.000
Use a case opener tool to carefully separate
the chrome bezal from the case of the phone.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
With the bezal gone the keypad is easily removed.

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:25.000
You can remove 4 more T5 screws holding the
main board into the back case.

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:58.000
After disconnecting 1 ribbon cable on top
of the unit the entire main board and screen
is easily removed from the back case

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:21.000
Next, remove the track pad by disconnecting
the ribbon cable on the back and pulling the
ribbon through the hole in the board.

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:43.000
Disconnect the ribbon for the lcd on the back
of the board

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:14.000
The LCD is held to the front of the main board
with adhesive and metal brackets. Using a
case opener tool pull back the brackets at
the top of the LCD. Very carefully pry the
LCD up and pull it out from the brackets at
the bottom.

